SetChoreVerboseMessages.description: SetChoreVerboseMessages is used to turn on (or off) more verbose reporting of messages to the Tm1s.log file. You can use this function to debug chores in which several processes call each other with the ExecuteProcess function.

SetDimensionGroupsSecurity.description: SetDimensionGroupsSecurity sets the security level for all existing groups for the specified dimension.

SetElementGroupsSecurity.description: SetElementGroupsSecurity sets the security level for a specified element in a dimension.

SetHierarchyElementGroupsSecurity.description: SetHierarchyElementGroupsSecurity sets the security level for a specified element from a hierarchy in a dimension.

SetHierarchyGroupsSecurity.description: SetHierarchyGroupsSecurity sets the security level for all existing groups for the specified dimension hierarchy.

SetInputCharacterSet.description: SetInputCharacterSet function lets you specify the character set used in a TurboIntegrator data source.

SetODBCUnicodeInterface.description: SetODBCUnicodeInterface sets whether the ODBC interface should use the Unicode wide functions or the regular single-byte character functions. Setting this function to 1 uses the wide character ODBC interface.

SetOutputCharacterSet.description: SetOutputCharacterSet lets you specify the character set to be used when writing to a text file using TextOutput in a TurboIntegrator proces.

SetOutputEscapeDoubleQuote.description: SetOutputEscapeDoubleQuote allows you to escape double quotes that appear in element names or data values when exporting a cube view to a .csv file.

SetUseActiveSandboxProperty.description: SetUseActiveSandboxProperty controls whether a process reads and writes cube data to the base data or to the user's active sandbox. The default is for processes to read and write to the base data.

StringGlobalVariable.description: Use this function to define a string global variable.

StringToNumber.description: StringToNumber converts a string to a number

StringToNumberEx.description: StringToNumberEx converts a string to a number

SubsetAliasSet.description: SubsetAliasSet sets the alias attribute to be used in a subset. SubsetAliasSet returns 1 if successful

SubsetAttrDelete.description: SubsetAttrDelete deletes a subset attribute from the TM1 database.

SubsetAttrInsert.description: SubsetAttrInsert creates a new attribute for subsets on your TM1 server. The function creates a string

SubsetATTRN.description: SubsetATTRN returns a numeric attribute for a specified subset.

SubsetATTRNL.description: SubsetATTRNL returns an attribute's numeric value for a specified subset with respect to a given locale.

SubsetAttrPutN.description: SubsetAttrPutN assigns a numeric value to an attribute for a specified subset.

SubsetAttrPutS.description: SubsetAttrPutS assigns a string value to an attribute for a specified subset.

SubsetATTRS.description: SubsetATTRS returns a string attribute for a specified subset.

SubsetATTRSL.description: SubsetATTRSL returns an attribute's string value for a specified subset with respect to a given locale.

SubsetCreate.description: SubsetCreate creates an empty public subset of a specified dimension.

SubsetCreateByMDX.description: SubsetCreateByMDX creates a public subset based on a passed MDX expression.

SubsetDeleteAllElements.description: SubsetDeleteAllElements deletes all elements from a public subset.

SubsetDestroy.description: SubsetDestroy deletes a subset from the TM1 database.

SubsetElementDelete.description: SubsetElementDelete deletes an element from a subset.

SubsetElementExists.description: SubsetElementExists determines whether a specific element exists within a specific public subset on the server from which a TurboIntegrator process is executed. SubsetElementExists cannot be used to determine if an element exists in a private subset.

SubsetElementGetIndex.description: SubsetElementGetIndex retrieves the index of an element in a subset. The function returns the index of the first occurrence of the specified element.

SubsetElementInsert.description: SubsetElementInsert adds an element to an existing subset.

SubsetExists.description: SubsetExists determines whether a specific public subset exists on the server from which a TurboIntegrator process is executed.

SubsetExpandAboveSet.description: SubsetExpandAboveSet sets the Expand Above property for a subset. The function returns 1 if successful

SubsetFormatStyleSet.description: SubsetFormatStyleSet applies an existing display style to a named subset.

SubsetGetElementName.description: SubsetGetElementName returns the name of the element at a specified index location within a given subset.

SubsetGetSize.description: SubsetGetSize returns the number of elements in a subset.

SubsetIsAllSet.description: SubsetIsAllSet sets a subset to use all elements of the parent dimension. SubsetIsAllSet returns 1 if successful

SubsetMDXGet.description: SubsetMDXGet retrieves the MDX expression used to create a subset.

SubsetMDXSet.description: SubsetMDXSet applies a specified MDX expression to an existing public subset.

Synchronized.description: Synchronized is used in a TurboIntegrator script to force serial execution of a designated set of TurboIntegrator processes.

TextOutput.description: TextOutput writes a comma-delimited record to a text file.

TM1User.description: TM1User returns a string giving the current TM1 client. When executed in a process that the user is running directly

ViewAttrDelete.description: ViewAttrDelete deletes a view attribute for a specific cube from the TM1 database.

ViewAttrInsert.description: ViewAttrInsert creates a new attribute for views of a specific cube on your TM1 server. The function can create a string

ViewAttrN.description: ViewAttrN returns a numeric attribute for a specified view.

ViewAttrNL.description: ViewAttrNL returns an attribute's numeric value for a specified view with respect to a given locale.

ViewAttrPutN.description: ViewAttrPutN assigns a value to a numeric view attribute.

ViewAttrPutS.description: ViewAttrPutS assigns a string value to an attribute for a specified view.

ViewAttrS.description: ViewAttrS returns a string attribute for a specified view.

ViewAttrSL.description: ViewAttrSL returns an attribute's string value for a specified view with respect to a given locale.

ViewColumnDimensionSet.description: ViewColumnDimensionSet sets a column dimension for a TM1 view.

ViewColumnSuppressZeroesSet.description: ViewColumnSuppressZeroesSet suppresses or enables the display of columns containing only zero values in a TM1 cube view.

ViewCreate.description: ViewCreate creates an empty view of a specified cube.

ViewCreateByMDX.description: ViewCreateByMDX creates a view with a specified MDX expression.

ViewDestroy.description: ViewDestroy deletes a view from the TM1 database.

ViewExists.description: ViewExists determines whether a specific public view exists on the server from which a TurboIntegrator process is executed. The function returns 1 if the view exists on the server

ViewExtractFilterByTitlesSet.description: ViewExtractFilterByTitlesSet sets an option to filter by titles on consolidated values that are excluded from a view or any associated view extracts.

ViewExtractSkipCalcsSet.description: ViewExtractSkipCalcsSet sets an option to include/exclude consolidated values in a viewÂ andÂ any associated view extracts. A view extract is a TM1 view exported as an ASCII comma-delimited (.cma) file.

ViewExtractSkipConsolidatedStringsSet.description: ViewExtractSkipConsolidatedStringsSet sets an option to exclude strings on consolidated values that are excluded from a view or any associated view extracts. A view extract is a TM1 view exported as an ASCII comma-delimited (.cma) file.

ViewExtractSkipRuleValuesSet.description: ViewExtractSkipRuleValuesSet sets an option to include/exclude rule-calculated values in a viewÂ andÂ any associated view extracts. A view extract is a TM1 view exported as an ASCII comma-delimited (.cma) file.

ViewExtractSkipZeroesSet.description: ViewExtractSkipZeroesSet sets an option to include/exclude zero values in a viewÂ andÂ any associated view extracts. A view extract is a TM1 view exported as an ASCII comma-delimited (.cma) file.

ViewMDXGet.description: ViewMDXGet retrieves the MDX expression for an existing MDX view.

ViewMDXSet.description: ViewMDXSet sets the MDX expression for an existing MDX view.

ViewRowDimensionSet.description: ViewRowDimensionSet sets a row dimension for a TM1 view.

ViewRowSuppressZeroesSet.description: ViewRowSuppressZeroesSet suppresses or enables the display of rows containing only zero values in a TM1 cube view.

ViewSubsetAssign.description: ViewSubsetAssign assigns a named subset to a cube view.

ViewSuppressZeroesSet.description: ViewSuppressZeroesSet suppresses or enables the display of all rows and columns containing only zero values in a TM1 cube view.

ViewTitleDimensionSet.description: ViewTitleDimensionSet sets a title dimension for a TM1 view.

ViewTitleElementSet.description: ViewTitleElementSet sets a title element for a TM1 view. ViewTitleElementSet is used in conjunction with the ViewTitleDimensionSet function.

ViewZeroOut.description: ViewZeroOut sets all data points in a view to zero.

While.description: The While statement allows a process to repeat a series of statements while a given condition is true. While statements can be nested.

WildcardFileSearch.description: WildcardFileSearch lets you use wildcard characters to search for files in a specified directory.

ProcessExitByBreak.description: Indicates that the process exited because it encountered a ProcessBreak function.

ProcessExitByChoreQuit.description: Indicates that the process exited due to execution of the ChoreQuit function.

ProcessExitByChoreRollback.description: Indicates that the process exited because it encountered a ChoreRollback function.

ProcessExitByProcessRollback.description: Indicates that the process exited because it encountered a ProcessRollback function.

ProcessExitByQuit.description: Indicates that the process exited because of an explicitÂ quitÂ command.

ProcessExitMinorError.description: Indicates that the process executed successfully but encountered minor errors.

ProcessExitNormal.description: Indicates that the process executed normally.

ProcessExitOnInit.description: Indicates that the process aborted during initialization.

ProcessExitSeriousError.description: Indicates that the process exited because of a serious error.

ProcessExitWithMessage.description: Indicates that the process exited normally with a message written toÂ tm1server.log.

ATTRN.description: ATTRN returns a numeric attribute for a specified element of a dimension.

ATTRS.description: ATTRS returns a string attribute for a specified element of a dimension.

CubeATTRN.description: CubeATTRN returns a numeric attribute for a specified cube.

CubeATTRS.description: CubeATTRS returns a string attribute for a specified cube.

DimensionATTRN.description: DimensionATTRN returns a numeric attribute for a specified dimension.

DimensionATTRS.description: DimensionATTRS returns a string attribute for a specified dimension.

ElementAttrN.description: ElementAttrN returns a numeric attribute for a specified element of a dimension.

ElementAttrS.description: ElementAttrS returns a string attribute for a specified element of a dimension.

ConsolidatedAvg.description: ConsolidatedAvg calculates the average value in a consolidation and returns that single value.

ConsolidateChildren.description: ConsolidateChildren forces consolidated values to be calculated by summing immediate children along a specified dimension. ConsolidateChildren is useful when intermediate consolidations are calculated by rules and you want a parent consolidation to be calculated by summing the intermediate consolidations rather than by summing the underlying leaf values.

ConsolidatedCount.description: ConsolidatedCount returns the number of values in a consolidation.

ConsolidatedCountUnique.description: ConsolidatedCountUnique counts the number of unique elements for which data points actually exist for the specified consolidation. The unique elements are counted along one dimension of the consolidated cell.

ConsolidatedMax.description: ConsolidatedMax calculates the maximum value in a consolidation and returns that single value.

ConsolidatedMin.description: ConsolidatedMin calculates the minimum value in a consolidation and returns that single value.

DB.description: DB returns a value from a cube in a TM1 database. DB returns a numeric value if used in a numeric expression and a string value if used in a string expression.

ISLEAF.description: ISLEAF returns 1 if a specified cell is a leaf cell (identified solely by leaf/simple elements). If the specified cell is identified by any consolidated elements, the function returns 0.

ISUNDEFINEDCELLVALUE.description: ISUNDEFINEDCELLVALUE compares the passed value to the default numeric cube value, which is influenced by the presence of the UNDEFVALS declaration in that cube's rule. The function returns 1 if the passed value equals the cube's default value, otherwise the function returns 0.

UNDEF.description: UNDEF returns the undefined value. This function can be used to prevent datafrom being stored in a cube based on a logical test.

UNDEFINEDCELLVALUE.description: UNDEFINEDCELLVALUE returns the default numeric cube value, which is influenced by the presence of the UNDEFVALS declaration in that cube's rule.

UNDEFVALS.description: Putting UNDEFVALS in the rules for a cube changes the default value for the cube from zero to aÂ special undefinedÂ value. Like other rules functions, UNDEFVALS applies only to the cube associated with the rule in which the function appears.

DATE.description: DATE returns the date string inÂ yy-mm-ddÂ orÂ yyyy-mm-ddÂ format for a given serial number.

DATES.description: DATES returns a date string, in the form 'yy-mm-dd' or 'yyyy-mm-dd', corresponding to a given year, month, and day.

DAY.description: DAY returns a numeric value for the day in a given date string.

DAYNO.description: DAYNO returns the serial date number corresponding to a given date string.

MONTH.description: MONTH returns a numeric value for the month in a given date string.

NOW.description: NOW returns the current date/time value in serial number format.

TIME.description: TIME returns a string, in HH:MM format, representing the system time on the TM1 server.

TIMST.description: TIMST returns a formatted date/time string.

TIMVL.description: TIMVL returns the numeric value of a component (year, month, etc.) of a date/time value.

TODAY.description: TODAY returns the current date in yy-mm-dd format.

YEAR.description: YEAR returns a numeric value for the year in a given date string.

DIMIX.description: DIMIX returns the index number of an element within a dimension.

DIMNM.description: DIMNM returns the element of a dimension that corresponds to the index argument.

DIMSIZ.description: DIMSIZ returns the number of elements within a specified dimension.

DNEXT.description: DNEXT returns the element name that follows the element specified as an argument to the function.

DNLEV.description: DNLEV returns the number levels in a dimension.

DTYPE.description: DTYPE returns information about the element type of a specified element. DTYPE returns N if the element is a numeric element, S if the element is a string element, and C if the element is a consolidated element.

TABDIM.description: TABDIM returns the dimension name that corresponds to the index argument.

ELCOMP.description: ELCOMP returns the name of a child of a consolidated element in a specified dimension.

ELCOMPN.description: ELCOMPN returns the number of components in a specified element. If the element argument is not a consolidated element, the function returns 0.

ElementComponent.description: ElementComponent returns the name of a child of a consolidated element in a specified dimension. If the element argument is not a consolidated element, the function returns 0.

ElementComponentCount.description: ElementComponentCount returns the number of components in a specified element. If the element argument is not a consolidated element, the function returns 0.

ElementCount.description: ElementCount returns the number of elements within a specified dimension.

ElementFirst.description: ElementFirst returns the first element of a specified dimension.

ElementIndex.description: ElementIndex returns the index number of an element within a dimension.

ElementIsAncestor.description: ElementIsAncestor determines whether element1 is an ancestor of element2 in the specified dimension. The function returns 1 if element1 is an ancestor of element2, otherwise the function returns 0.

ElementIsComponent.description: ElementIsComponent determines whether element1 is a child of element2 in the specified dimension. The function returns 1 if element1 is a child of element2, otherwise the function returns 0.

ElementIsParent.description: ElementIsParent determines whether element1 is a parent of element2 in the specified dimension. The function returns 1 if element1 is a parent of element2, otherwise the function returns 0.

ElementLevel.description: ElementLevel returns the level of an element within a dimension.

ElementName.description: ElementName returns the element of a dimension that corresponds to the index argument.

ElementNext.description: ElementNext returns the element name that follows the element specified as an argument to the function.

ElementParent.description: ElementParent returns the parent of an element in a specified dimension.

ElementParentCount.description: ElementParentCount returns the number of parents of an element in a specified dimension.

ElementType.description: ElementType returns information about the element type of a specified element. ElementType returns N if the element is a numeric element, S if the element is a string element, and C if the element is a consolidated element.

ElementWeight.description: ElementWeight returns the weight of a child in a consolidated element.

ELISANC.description: ELISANC determines whether element1 is an ancestor of element2 in the specified dimension. The function returns 1 if element1 is an ancestor of element2, otherwise the function returns 0.

ELISCOMP.description: ELISCOMP determines whether element1 is a child of element2 in the specified dimension. The function returns 1 if element1 is a child of element2, otherwise the function returns 0.

ELISPAR.description: ELISPAR determines whether element1 is a parent of element2 in the specified dimension. The function returns 1 if element1 is a parent of element2, otherwise the function returns 0.

ELLEV.description: ELLEV returns the level of an element within a dimension.

ELPAR.description: ELPAR returns the parent of an element in a specified dimension.

ELPARN.description: ELPARN returns the number of parents of an element in a specified dimension.

ELWEIGHT.description: ELWEIGHT returns the weight of a child in a consolidated element.

LevelCount.description: LevelCount returns the number levels in a dimension.

FV.description: FV returns the value of an annuity at the time of the last payment. An annuity is a series of payments made at equal intervals of time. Payments are assumed to be made at the end of each period.

PAYMT.description: PAYMT returns the payment amount of an annuity based on a given initial value or principal, an interest rate, and a number of periods. An annuity is a series of payments made at equal intervals of time.

PV.description: PV returns the initial or principal value of an annuity.

RAND.description: RAND generates a random number that is uniformly distributed between 0 and 1. The random number generator is seeded when TM1 is loaded.

ABS.description: ABS returns the absolute value of a number.

ACOS.description: ACOS returns the angle, in radians, whose cosine is x.

ASIN.description: ASIN returns the angle, in radians, whose sine is x.

ATAN.description: ATAN returns the angle, in radians, whose tangent is x. The result is between -pi/2 and +pi/2.

COS.description: COS returns the cosine of an angle expressed in radians.

EXP.description: EXP returns the natural anti-log of a number.

INT.description: INT returns the largest integer that is less than or equal to a specified value.

ISUND.description: ISUND returns 1 if a specified value is undefined; otherwise it returns 0.

LN.description: LN returns the natural logarithm (base e) of a number.

LOG.description: LOG returns the base 10 logarithm of a positive number.

MAX.description: MAX returns the largest number in a pair of values.

MIN.description: MIN returns the smallest number in a pair of values.

MOD.description: MOD returns the remainder of dividing a number by a divisor.

ROUND.description: ROUND rounds a given number to the nearest integer. Rounding can be done in a variety of valid ways.

ROUNDP.description: ROUNDP rounds a given number at a specified decimal precision.

SIGN.description: SIGN determines if a number is positive, negative, or zero. The function returns 1 if the number is positive, -1 if the number is negative, and 0 if the number is zero.

SIN.description: SIN returns the sine of a given angle.

SQRT.description: SQRT returns the square root of a given value.

TAN.description: TAN returns the tangent of a given angle.

CAPIT.description: CAPIT applies initial capitalization to every word in a string.

CHAR.description: CHAR returns the character identified by a given ASCII numeric code.

CODE.description: CODE returns the ASCII numeric code for a specified character within a string.

DELET.description: DELET returns the result of deleting a specified number of characters from a specified starting point within a string.

FILL.description: FILL repeats a given string as necessary to return a string of a specified length.

INSRT.description: INSRT inserts one string into another string at a specified insertion point.

LONG.description: LONG returns the length of a string.

LOWER.description: LOWER converts all upper case characters in a string to lower case.

NUMBR.description: NUMBR converts a string to a number. The string passed to the NUMBR function must use. (period) as the decimal separator and , (comma) as the thousand separator. Any other decimal/thousand separators will cause incorrect results.

SCAN.description: SCAN returns a number indicating the starting location of the first occurrence of a specified substring within a string. If the substring does not occur in the given string, the function returns 0.

STR.description: STR converts a number to a string.

SUBST.description: SUBST returns a substring of a given string.

TRIM.description: TRIM returns the result of trimming any leading and trailing blanks from a string.

UPPER.description: UPPER converts a text string to upper case.
